			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Company:</strong></p>
<p>
Signpost is a leading online advertising startup that connects local businesses with new customers. We offer a simple solution to help small businesses manage all of their online advertising through a single platform. At the same time, we&rsquo;re making it easier for mobile and online publishers to source relevant ad content from local businesses. We believe we&rsquo;re creating an efficient advertising tool that will significantly change the $20B local advertising industry. Along with working hard, we also believe in creating a work environment that gets you excited to wake up in the morning.<br />
Signpost is funded by Google Ventures, Spark Capital (Foursquare, Twitter, Tumblr) and a group of accomplished angel investors including Jason Calacanis (Mahalo, Launch Conference), Jack Herrick (eHow) and Thomas Lehrman (Gerson Lehrman).</p>
<p>
To learn more about Signpost, check out press we received in TechCrunch, Portfolio, and Business Insider or visit our website: www.signpost.com.</p>
<p>
<strong>Opportunity:</strong></p>
<p>
As a Sales Representative at Signpost you&rsquo;ll have the opportunity to significantly contribute to the growth of our business. We&rsquo;re a young start-up with a small, but growing team. You will interact with senior management and provide input on the sales process and product at Signpost. This is a huge opportunity to join an exciting startup company at an early stage with potential for explosive growth and great financial reward.</p>
<p>
This job will be based in New York, NY. We offer a competitive compensation package including base and commission. If you are ready to work for a fun, fast-paced startup, please send us your resume!</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop and cultivate leads through your pipeline from prospecting and qualifying, to negotiating and closing.</li>
<li>
High volume outbound calling to potential merchants across the country.</li>
<li>
Persuasively articulate Signpost&rsquo;s service, benefits, and processes to potential targets.</li>
<li>
Meet monthly sales targets according to sales plan.</li>
<li>
Participate in weekly sales meetings and articulate market feedback to Signpost&rsquo;s senior executives.</li>
<li>
Take on higher-level tasks as needed.<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Ideal qualifications include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
0-2&nbsp;years of sales experience.</li>
<li>
Ability to thrive in an ever-changing, fast-paced environment.</li>
<li>
Exceptional communication skills both written and oral.</li>
<li>
Ability to work autonomously while maintaining focus and work ethic.</li>
</ul>
